<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1037,151,177]" box="[151,1037,151,177]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,1037,151,177]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,1037,151,177]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker. A" authorityYear="1857" box="[412,516,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[412,516,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Rhotana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[592,774,151,177]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Java, Sumatra</collectingRegion>
and adjacent islands
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="107" pageNumber="108" type="key">
<key pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyStep pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" box="[151,1436,223,244]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,223,244]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
1. Forewings with prominent black mark(s) near hind margin distad of clavus (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[998,1087,223,244]" captionStart="FIGURE 232" captionStartId="261.[151,244,1688,1709]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,1056,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-39@261.[176,1411,1048,1667]" captionTargetPageId="261" captionText="FIGURE 232. Rhotana pavo (Decora pavo Bierman, holotype ♂)." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Fig. 232f</figureCitation>
)........................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" box="[151,1436,253,274]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,253,274]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">- Forewings without such mark(s) distad of clavus............................................................. 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" box="[151,1436,282,303]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,282,303]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
2. 7-8 distinct forewing marks separated by a red stripe (
<figureCitation box="[743,833,282,303]" captionStart="FIGURE 232" captionStartId="261.[151,244,1688,1709]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,1056,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-39@261.[176,1411,1048,1667]" captionTargetPageId="261" captionText="FIGURE 232. Rhotana pavo (Decora pavo Bierman, holotype ♂)." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Fig. 232f</figureCitation>
)............... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bierman)" authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Bierman" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1041,1218,282,303]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pavo">
<emphasis box="[1041,1115,282,303]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. pavo</emphasis>
(Bierman)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Bierman" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1233,1306,282,303]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pavo">
<emphasis box="[1233,1306,282,303]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. pavo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group), p. 92
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
- One elongated black forewing mark, containing three white spots (
<figureCitation box="[864,942,311,332]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 and 34" captionStartId="199.[151,258,846,867]" captionTargetBox="[263,1322,155,777]" captionTargetId="figure-115@199.[263,1324,155,777]" captionTargetPageId="199" captionText="FIGURES 33 and 34. Rhotana marmorata, live specimen from Singapore (courtesy Cheong Loong Fah), the identification was based on the photo only and is therefore uncertain." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Figs. 33</figureCitation>
and 34)................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Zelazny" authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" box="[1021,1239,341,362]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[1021,1156,341,362]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. marmorata</emphasis>
Zelazny
</taxonomicName>
(ungrouped), p. 101
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
3. Basal half of forewings infuscated, most of apical half clear, but with dark stripe(s) accompanying apical cross-veins (e.g. 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 249" captionStartId="268.[151,244,1636,1657]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,877,1600]" captionTargetId="figure-37@268.[178,1409,868,1615]" captionTargetPageId="268" captionText="FIGURE 249. Rhotana semiopalina, holotype ♂." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Figs. 249f</figureCitation>
or 197f)......................................................................................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" box="[151,1436,429,450]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,429,450]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">- Forewings without dark stripes accompanying apical cross-veins................................................ 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
4. Forewings with infuscated band along apical cross-veins very narrow (
<figureCitation box="[904,996,458,479]" captionStart="FIGURE 249" captionStartId="268.[151,244,1636,1657]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,877,1600]" captionTargetId="figure-37@268.[178,1409,868,1615]" captionTargetPageId="268" captionText="FIGURE 249. Rhotana semiopalina, holotype ♂." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Fig. 249f</figureCitation>
), male genital styles elongated, triangular and pointed (
<figureCitation box="[310,398,487,508]" captionStart="FIGURE 249" captionStartId="268.[151,244,1636,1657]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,877,1600]" captionTargetId="figure-37@268.[178,1409,868,1615]" captionTargetPageId="268" captionText="FIGURE 249. Rhotana semiopalina, holotype ♂." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Fig. 249i</figureCitation>
).................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Muir" authorityName="Muir" authorityYear="1926" box="[1042,1239,487,509]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semiopalina">
<emphasis box="[1042,1185,488,509]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. semiopalina</emphasis>
Muir
</taxonomicName>
(ungrouped), p. 103
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" box="[151,1436,517,538]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,517,538]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
- Forewings with apical cross-veins lined by two distinct infuscated stripes, some distance from cross-veins (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[1295,1385,517,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 199" captionStartId="247.[151,244,1695,1716]" captionTargetBox="[176,1418,1064,1647]" captionTargetId="figure-46@247.[148,1438,1042,1658]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 199. Rhotana transversolinea: f, g holotype ♂; i–p Rhotana bicolor Muir, holotype ♂." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Fig. 199f</figureCitation>
).. 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
5. Hindwings with a black spot around base of Ms2 and several dark stripes across apical third of wing (
<figureCitation box="[1199,1293,546,567]" captionStart="FIGURE 197" captionStartId="246.[151,244,1991,2012]" captionTargetBox="[198,1363,1363,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-51@246.[198,1379,1354,1986]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 197. Rhotana jacobsoni, holotype ♂." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1244,1293,546,567]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.97" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" unit="g" value="197.0">197g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
)........................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Zelazny &amp; Webb, 2011" authorityName="Zelazny &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2011" box="[963,1083,576,597]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacobsoni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[963,1083,576,597]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. jacobsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1089,1164,575,596]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1914" box="[1177,1306,576,597]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosana">
<emphasis box="[1177,1306,576,597]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. formosana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group), p. 69
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
- Hindwings with two black spots around base of Ms2, but without dark stripes (
<figureCitation box="[982,1076,605,626]" captionStart="FIGURE 199" captionStartId="247.[151,244,1695,1716]" captionTargetBox="[176,1418,1064,1647]" captionTargetId="figure-46@247.[148,1438,1042,1658]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 199. Rhotana transversolinea: f, g holotype ♂; i–p Rhotana bicolor Muir, holotype ♂." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1026,1076,605,626]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.9899999999999998" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" unit="g" value="199.0">199g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
).................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Melichar" authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1914" box="[894,1163,634,655]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversolinea">
<emphasis box="[894,1070,634,655]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. transversolinea</emphasis>
Melichar
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1914" box="[1177,1306,634,655]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosana">
<emphasis box="[1177,1306,634,655]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. formosana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group), p. 70
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
6. Forewings mottled with faint infuscation, a red mark around last subcostal sector (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1104,663,684]" captionStart="FIGURE 253" captionStartId="270.[151,244,982,1003]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,202,943]" captionTargetId="figure-71@270.[178,1409,191,961]" captionTargetPageId="270" captionText="FIGURE 253. Rhotana venosa, a–r lectotype ♂; remainder: apical parts of aedeagus in dorsal views of specimen from: s, Laos; t, Verlaten Isl.; u, Tawau, Borneo; v, Sarawak. Borneo; w, Tawau, Borneo; x, Ranau, Borneo." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Fig. 253f</figureCitation>
)................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1906" box="[1071,1239,693,714]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venosa">
<emphasis box="[1071,1164,693,714]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. venosa</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
(ungrouped), p. 105
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,223,802]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<keyLead pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
- Forewings colourless with some dark spots in basal quarter, at apex of Cu, and around last subcostal sector (
<figureCitation box="[1269,1362,722,743]" captionStart="FIGURE 217" captionStartId="255.[151,244,1151,1172]" captionTargetBox="[189,1407,632,1138]" captionTargetId="figure-54@255.[176,1411,621,1148]" captionTargetPageId="255" captionText="FIGURE 217. Rhotana ramosa, holotype ♂." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Fig. 217f</figureCitation>
); apical part of male aedeagus with two processes, each ending in numerous branched processes (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1216,751,772]" captionStart="FIGURE 217" captionStartId="255.[151,244,1151,1172]" captionTargetBox="[189,1407,632,1138]" captionTargetId="figure-54@255.[176,1411,621,1148]" captionTargetPageId="255" captionText="FIGURE 217. Rhotana ramosa, holotype ♂." pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
Figs. 
<quantity box="[1134,1191,751,772]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.17" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" unit="m" value="217.0">217m</quantity>
, p
</figureCitation>
).................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Zelazny &amp; Webb, 2011" authorityName="Zelazny &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2011" box="[1023,1122,781,802]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1023,1122,781,802]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. ramosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1128,1202,781,802]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" box="[1215,1306,781,802]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis box="[1215,1306,781,802]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">R. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group), p. 83
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
